## Common Patterns

### Styling Attributes

Most components support these common styling attributes:

- `color` (Symbol) - DaisyUI semantic colors (`:primary`, `:secondary`, `:success`, `:error`, etc.)
- `size` (Symbol) - Size variants (`:xs`, `:sm`, `:md`, `:lg`, `:xl`)
- `variant` (Symbol) - Style variants (`:filled`, `:outlined`, `:ghost`, etc.)
- `disabled` (Boolean) - Disable interaction

### Form Field Attributes

Form components inherit extensive common attributes from `FormField` base class:

**Basic Attributes:**
- `name` (String) - Input name attribute
- `label` (String) - Field label
- `required` (Boolean) - Required field indicator
- `disabled` (Boolean) - Disabled state
- `helper_text` (String) - Help text below field
- `placeholder` (String) - Placeholder text

**Extended FormField Attributes (available on most form components):**
- `description` (String) - Description under label
- `autocomplete` (String) - Autocomplete hint
- `compact` (Boolean) - Compact styling
- `collapsing_helper_text` (Boolean) - Collapsible helper text
- `floating_error_text` (Boolean) - Floating error messages
- `hide_required_asterisk` (Boolean) - Hide required indicator
- `valid_label_classes`/`invalid_label_classes` (String) - Custom label styling
- `control_actions`/`control_targets` (Array) - Stimulus configuration
- `control_html_options` (Hash) - Additional HTML options
- `form_control_controller_path` (String) - Custom Stimulus controller
- `error_messages` (Array) - Error message array
- `validations`/`validation_messages` (Hash) - Validation configuration

**FormChild Attributes (layout):**
- `label_position` (Symbol) - `:top`, `:left`, `:right`, `:inline`, `:inside`
- `grid_span` (Symbol) - Grid layout spans

**CheckableFormField (Checkbox/Radio):**
- `label_position` (Symbol) - Label positioning
- Additional checkable-specific attributes

### Navigation Patterns

Navigation components use consistent slot patterns:

```ruby
# Common navigation pattern
render Decor::Nav::SideNavbar.new do |navbar|
  navbar.with_section(title: "Section") do |section|
    section.with_item(title: "Item", path: "/path")  # Use 'path', not 'href'
  end
end
```

**Note:** Page components (`Page`, `PageHeader`, `PageSection`) are in the root `Decor` namespace, not `Decor::Nav`.

